Share with:
Trade Marketing Manager Job (Consumer Goods), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Sales
Industry:
Consumer Goods / FMCG
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
29 April 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of one of the world’s leading consumer goods and personal care companies. Our respected client is seeking a sales and marketing professional, preferably with experience working in a multinational consumer goods or pharmaceutical company, for the job of Trade Marketing Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The winning candidate will report directly to the Head of Trade Marketing.
Key job responsibilities will include:
Plays a key role within the Country Sales team, driving excellence in store (4P) execution across key customers/key account
Focusing on building expert knowledge in our key categories and sharing this with the customer in order to build long-term partnerships and increase profit and sales
Leads within the country the development and implementation of category management strategies, this will focus on increasing the company’s in store presence in our categories, strengthening our brands, optimizing product assortment, and promotional strategy
The role holder has constant interaction with the Marketing and the Sales team
Externally s/he interacts with the Wholesalers, Distributors and the Key Accounts
Delivery of category and  channel P&L as per company objectives
Developing a 4P/3D category and channel master plan with distinct KPIs and ROIs in line with the marketing master plan to deliver the annual P&L. The plan is to be developed in consultation with various stake holders like marketing/field sales. The annual master plan is then to be split into monthly deliverables
Develop NPD/EPD launch plans for one's own category/channel
Develop channel specific and category specific POSM in line with the guidelines at minimum cost.
Develop allocation of consumer promos in line with the strategic intent
Planning for tactical response in case of competitive threats or opportunities
Assist the sales team in improving their efficiency by equipping them with tools/selling stories and  developing training modules for the same
Localize global 4P strategies and principles; convert global success models into local success models
Designing KPIs for various players like DBSRs/SPGs/RB Field force on efficiency
Monitoring the performance of initiatives in Sales Master Plan against the KPIs, course correcting for deviations.
Trade investment  to be in line with the financial plan
Develop effective communication packages on a monthly/quarterly basis so as to facilitate the sales team to communicate the various trade programs and consumer promos with the key beneficiaries in the best possible manner
Identification of key sales issues and taking the right action promptly
Continuously seeking opportunities to grow the business in sync with the market plan
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree (min.) in sales, marketing, or business administration with a Master degree in business administration preferred
At least 4-5 Years of mandatory field experience + existing key accounts, trade marketing, brand management experience with FMCG or pharmaceutical company
Strong knowledge of field sales and trade marketing
Results oriented, entrepreneurial and self-motivated
Tenacious and resilient, driven to achieve even when faced with obstacles
Leadership and interpersonal skills capable of building strong working relationships and influencing and customers and internal teams
Creative and innovative in designing schemes
Sound commercial understanding of business issues, opportunities
Clear understanding of sales and marketing strategy and planning issues
Strong analytical skills with ability to develop strategies, tactics and measurable implementation
Able to speak fluently in English
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.